1. Go to your VM in the Azure portal, stop the VM to ensure data consistency during the snapshot.
2. Navigate to the Disks section of the VM.
3. Select the OS disk.
4. Choose Create snapshot.
5. Specify the snapshot name, select Full snapshot type, and save.
6. Create a Managed Disk from Snapshot:
7. Go to Snapshots under Disks in the Azure portal.
8. Select the snapshot created and choose Create Disk.
9. Name the managed disk and configure its settings.
10. Create a VM from the Managed Disk:
11. Go to Virtual Machines and select Create.
12. Choose the Create a VM from a disk option.
13. Specify the managed disk created from the snapshot.
14. Configure the VM settings and complete the creation process.
